## Finding: Deterministic layout failures are repaired too late

### Violated goal
Compiler invariants should be enforced before Dart source exists; LLM repair must not compensate deterministic compiler/layout law failures.

### Failure family
Typed compiler model is incomplete, so post-emit regex surgery and repair loops become architectural crutches.

### Why this matters
If stack bounds, positioned constraints, widget class names, imports, text wrapping or runtime geometry are corrected after emit, the real invariant lives outside the compiler model. That makes failures harder to reproduce and easier to “fix” incorrectly.

### Systemic cause
The system still treats Dart text as an editable intermediate representation, then applies regex/string patches and sometimes sends geometry failures into the LLM repair loop.

### Evidence to look for
- Regex Dart surgery is explicitly forbidden but baselined: [lint_regex_dart_surgery.py](E:/@dev/figma-flutter-agent/scripts/lint_regex_dart_surgery.py:2), [regex_dart_surgery_baseline.txt](E:/@dev/figma-flutter-agent/tests/fixtures/lint/regex_dart_surgery_baseline.txt:1).
- Source-level Positioned fixes: [positioned.py](E:/@dev/figma-flutter-agent/src/figma_flutter_agent/generator/dart/llm_codegen/positioned.py:16), [positioned.py](E:/@dev/figma-flutter-agent/src/figma_flutter_agent/generator/dart/llm_codegen/positioned.py:102), [positioned.py](E:/@dev/figma-flutter-agent/src/figma_flutter_agent/generator/dart/llm_codegen/positioned.py:161).
- Runtime geometry errors are folded into repair input: [loop.py](E:/@dev/figma-flutter-agent/src/figma_flutter_agent/stages/llm_repair/loop.py:190), [loop.py](E:/@dev/figma-flutter-agent/src/figma_flutter_agent/stages/llm_repair/loop.py:203), [runtime_geometry_check.py](E:/@dev/figma-flutter-agent/src/figma_flutter_agent/stages/runtime_geometry_check.py:57).

### Correct architectural direction
Dart text should be a final serialization target, not a mutable IR. Geometry/layout constraints should be typed planner invariants with deterministic repair passes before emit.

### Recommended fix shape
Introduce a typed planned-Dart/layout graph and allow AST-sidecar transformations only on structured nodes. Classify repairable LLM mistakes separately from deterministic invariant failures; the latter should fail or route to deterministic layout passes.

### Priority
P1

### Confidence
Medium-High

## Finding: Gates can be green while accepted debt remains product-risky

### Violated goal
Release gates should measure product confidence, not only “no new known debt fingerprints”.

### Failure family
Baseline-driven validation and insufficient corpus coverage.

### Why this matters
A green signoff can mean “the debt did not grow”, not “the architecture now satisfies the stated goals”. Advisory/semantic-only failures and large accepted heuristic baselines can hide regressions in generalization.

### Systemic cause
Several linters and burndown checks compare against committed baselines; corpus oracle blocking criteria are based on a small curated subset, while advisory tiers do not block release.

### Evidence to look for
- Legacy semantics burndown accepts baseline fingerprints: [semantics_legacy_burndown.py](E:/@dev/figma-flutter-agent/scripts/semantics_legacy_burndown.py:194), [legacy_predicate_fingerprints.txt](E:/@dev/figma-flutter-agent/tests/fixtures/semantics/legacy_predicate_fingerprints.txt:1), [test_semantics_legacy_burndown.py](E:/@dev/figma-flutter-agent/tests/test_semantics_legacy_burndown.py:34).
